[4] USA (Alabama)
Date: Thu 2 Oct 2014
Source: Alabama 13 Birmingham [edited]
http://www.alabamas13.com/story/26685518/top-5-respiratory-virus-update-body-found-and-domestic-violence-awareness-month-top-your-thursday-morning-headlines


Children's of Alabama has confirmed that one patient has tested positive for enterovirus D-68. The rare respiratory illness is already blamed for the deaths of 3 children nationwide. The staff at Children's has sent about 20 other specimens to the CDC for testing.

[Byline: Robyn Sirman]

